        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 5:26PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 526 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Marion, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Marion, Morgan Springs, Folsom, and Judson College.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
